ENTRY       EC 2.4.1.96                 Enzyme
NAME        sn-glycerol-3-phosphate 1-galactosyltransferase;
            isofloridoside-phosphate synthase;
            UDP-Gal:sn-glycero-3-phosphoric acid 1-alpha-galactosyl-transferase;
            UDPgalactose:sn-glycerol-3-phosphate alpha-D-galactosyltransferase;
            uridine diphosphogalactose-glycerol phosphate galactosyltransferase;
            glycerol 3-phosphate 1alpha-galactosyltransferase;
            UDP-galactose:sn-glycerol-3-phosphate 1-alpha-D-galactosyltransferase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Glycosyltransferases;
            Hexosyltransferases
SYSNAME     UDP-alpha-D-galactose:sn-glycerol-3-phosphate 1-alpha-D-galactosyltransferase
REACTION    UDP-alpha-D-galactose + sn-glycerol 3-phosphate = UDP + 1-O-alpha-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate [RN:R00854]
ALL_REAC    R00854
SUBSTRATE   UDP-alpha-D-galactose [CPD:C00052];
            sn-glycerol 3-phosphate [CPD:C00093]
PRODUCT     UDP [CPD:C00015];
            1-O-alpha-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate [CPD:C04703]
COMMENT     The product is hydrolysed by a phosphatase to isofloridoside, which is involved in osmoregulation (cf. EC 2.4.1.137 sn-glycerol-3-phosphate 2-alpha-galactosyltransferase).
HISTORY     EC 2.4.1.96 created 1978
